<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:s="https://admin.wvusports.com/services/xml_schema/story" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>West Virginia University Athletics</title><link>https://admin.wvusports.com/rss.aspx</link><description>Latest news items for West Virginia University Athletics</description><atom:link href="https://admin.wvusports.com/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en-us</language><ttl>60</ttl><item><title>Mountaineers Defeat Kansas State to Advance in Big 12 Tournament</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/22/baseball-mountaineers-defeat-kansas-state-to-advance-in-big-12-tournament</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/22/baseball-mountaineers-defeat-kansas-state-to-advance-in-big-12-tournament</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Matthew Graveline celebrates after getting a hit against Kansas State in the Big 12 quarterfinals" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/21/DSC02936.jpeg" /><br /><br />SURPRISE, Ariz. – The ninth-ranked and No. 2-seed West Virginia University baseball team advanced to the Big 12 Tournament semifinals with a 4-2 win over Kansas State, Thursday night at Surprise Stadium. The Mountaineers improve to 38-13 overall while the Wildcats fall to 30-27.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/DSC02936.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/DSC02936.jpeg"><media:title>Matthew Graveline celebrates after getting a hit against Kansas State in the Big 12 quarterfinals</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/DSC02936.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 00:16:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59128</s:story_id></item><item><title>Eight Mountaineers Selected for NCAA East First Round</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/21/track-field-eight-mountaineers-selected-for-ncaa-east-first-round</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/21/track-field-eight-mountaineers-selected-for-ncaa-east-first-round</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Eight Mountaineers selected for the NCAA Outdoor Track and Field East First Round" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/21/TRACK26_OutdoorRegionalQualifiers_1920x1080.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Eight members of the West Virginia University track and field team have been selected to compete at the 2026 NCAA East First Round, held May 27-30 in Lexington, Kentucky.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/TRACK26_OutdoorRegionalQualifiers_1920x1080.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/TRACK26_OutdoorRegionalQualifiers_1920x1080.jpg"><media:title>Eight Mountaineers selected for the NCAA Outdoor Track and Field East First Round</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/TRACK26_OutdoorRegionalQualifiers_1920x1080.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 15:20:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>16</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59126</s:story_id></item><item><title>Players Era, MGM Resorts International and ESPN Announce Brackets and Tournament Arena Locations for 2026 Players Era Men’s Championships</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/21/mens-basketball-players-era-mgm-resorts-international-and-espn-announce-brackets-and-tournament-arena-locations-for-2026-players-era-mens-championships</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/21/mens-basketball-players-era-mgm-resorts-international-and-espn-announce-brackets-and-tournament-arena-locations-for-2026-players-era-mens-championships</guid><category>Men's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="A graphic for the 2026 Players Era 8 tournament" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/21/MBB26_PlayersEraMatchups_1920x1080.jpg" /><br /><br />NEW YORK/LAS VEGAS – Players Era, an EverWonder Studio company, MGM Resorts International, and ESPN today announced the brackets for the 2026 Players Era Men's Championships, with the Players Era 8 taking place Tuesday-Thursday, November 17-19, at Michelob ULTRA Arena at Mandalay Bay Resort and Casino in Las Vegas, and the Players Era 16 Championship set for Tuesday-Saturday, November 24-28, at T-Mobile Arena in Las Vegas and Michelob ULTRA Arena.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/MBB26_PlayersEraMatchups_1920x1080.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/MBB26_PlayersEraMatchups_1920x1080.jpg"><media:title>A graphic for the 2026 Players Era 8 tournament</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/MBB26_PlayersEraMatchups_1920x1080.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 13:43:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>4</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59125</s:story_id></item><item><title>WVU Varsity Club Accepting Memberships for 2026-27 Year</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/21/general-wvu-varsity-club-accepting-memberships-for-2026-27-year</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/21/general-wvu-varsity-club-accepting-memberships-for-2026-27-year</guid><category>General</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="WVU Varsity Club announces that they are accepting memberships for the 2026-27 year" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/21/1920x1080.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The WVU Varsity Club is now accepting memberships and renewals for the 2026-27 year for all former Mountaineer student-athletes and athletics administrators.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/1920x1080.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/1920x1080.jpg"><media:title>WVU Varsity Club announces that they are accepting memberships for the 2026-27 year</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/1920x1080.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 10:18:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>3</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59124</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia Set for Big 12 Tournament</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/20/baseball-west-virginia-set-for-big-12-tournament</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/20/baseball-west-virginia-set-for-big-12-tournament</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Matchup Big 12 Tournament" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/20/BB26_Big12TMatchup_1920x1080_QF.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 9 West Virginia University baseball team heads to Surprise, Arizona for the 2026 Big 12 Tournament. The first game for the Mountaineers at Surprise Stadium will be on Thursday, May 21, at 7:30 p.m. at Surprise Stadium against the winner of the No. 7-seed TCU and No. 11-seed Kansas State.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/20/BB26_Big12TMatchup_1920x1080_QF.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/20/BB26_Big12TMatchup_1920x1080_QF.jpg"><media:title>Matchup Big 12 Tournament</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/20/BB26_Big12TMatchup_1920x1080_QF.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 20 May 2026 19:08:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59123</s:story_id></item><item><title>Golf Finishes Strong at NCAA Regional</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/20/golf-finishes-strong-at-ncaa-regional</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/20/golf-finishes-strong-at-ncaa-regional</guid><category>Golf</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="WVU golf team at NCAA Regionals" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/20/GOLF_AZ_REGIONAL_RD3-13.jpg" /><br /><br />MARANA, Ariz. – West Virginia University golfer Nick Turowski shot -5 in the final round while senior Kaleb Wilson shot -4 today to lead the Mountaineers to their lowest score in an NCAA event at the NCAA Marana Regional at The Gallery Golf Club in Marana, Arizona, on Wednesday.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/20/GOLF_AZ_REGIONAL_RD3-13.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/20/GOLF_AZ_REGIONAL_RD3-13.jpg"><media:title>WVU golf team at NCAA Regionals</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/20/GOLF_AZ_REGIONAL_RD3-13.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 20 May 2026 18:40:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>5</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59122</s:story_id></item><item><title>WVU’s Baker Remains Bullish on Mountaineer Athletics</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/19/general-wvus-baker-remains-bullish-on-mountaineer-athletics</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/19/general-wvus-baker-remains-bullish-on-mountaineer-athletics</guid><category>General</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="WVU Vice President and Director of Athletics Wren Baker visits with media in the Team Room inside the Milan Puskar Center on Tuesday, May 19, 2026." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/19/Baker-Main_41J2u.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.VA. – Another successful athletic year is nearing its conclusion, which means it's time for West Virginia University Vice President and Director of Athletics Wren Baker to put a bow on things with his yearly spring visit with media.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/19/Baker-Main_41J2u.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/19/Baker-Main_41J2u.jpg"><media:title>WVU Vice President and Director of Athletics Wren Baker visits with media in the Team Room inside the Milan Puskar Center on Tuesday, May 19, 2026.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/19/Baker-Main_41J2u.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 19:57:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>3</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59121</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Shoot -6 on Moving Day</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/19/golf-mountaineers-shoot-6-on-moving-day</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/19/golf-mountaineers-shoot-6-on-moving-day</guid><category>Golf</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="The golf course at the NCAA Regional in Marana, Arizona." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/19/GOLF_AZ_REGIONAL_PRAC-25_Afiu3.jpg" /><br /><br />MARANA, Ariz. – The West Virginia University golf team shot 6-under-par on moving day to jump two spots in the team standings during the second round of the NCAA Marana Regional at The Gallery Golf Club in Marana, Arizona, on Tuesday.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/19/GOLF_AZ_REGIONAL_PRAC-25_Afiu3.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/19/GOLF_AZ_REGIONAL_PRAC-25_Afiu3.jpg"><media:title>The golf course at the NCAA Regional in Marana, Arizona.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/19/GOLF_AZ_REGIONAL_PRAC-25_Afiu3.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 18:32:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>5</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59120</s:story_id></item><item><title>Izzo-Brown Adds Clyburn and Gnädig to Fall Roster</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/19/womens-soccer-izzo-brown-adds-clyburn-and-gn-dig-to-fall-roster</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/19/womens-soccer-izzo-brown-adds-clyburn-and-gn-dig-to-fall-roster</guid><category>Women's Soccer</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="nikki izzo-brown" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2024/11/19/DSC01362.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – West Virginia University women's soccer coach Nikki Izzo-Brown has announced the addition of two student-athletes who will join the Mountaineer roster for the fall 2026 campaign.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2024/11/19/DSC01362.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2024/11/19/DSC01362.jpg"><media:title>nikki izzo-brown</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2024/11/19/DSC01362.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 15:50:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>13</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59119</s:story_id></item><item><title>Yehl Named Big 12 Pitcher of the Year, 10 Players Named All-Big 12</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/19/baseball-yehl-named-big-12-pitcher-of-the-year-10-players-named-all-big-12</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/19/baseball-yehl-named-big-12-pitcher-of-the-year-10-players-named-all-big-12</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Maxx Yehl throws a pitch against TCU" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/19/BSBvsKState_Game1_202_large.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Redshirt junior Maxx Yehl of the West Virginia University baseball team was named the 2026 Big 12 Pitcher of the Year, as announced by the conference on Tuesday.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/19/BSBvsKState_Game1_202_large.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/19/BSBvsKState_Game1_202_large.jpg"><media:title>Maxx Yehl throws a pitch against TCU</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/19/BSBvsKState_Game1_202_large.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 13:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59118</s:story_id></item></channel></rss>